verses.verse: To the chief Musician<WH5329> on Neginoth,<WH5058> A Psalm<WH4210> or Song.<WH7892> God<WH430> be merciful<WH2603> unto us, and bless<WH1288> us; and cause his face<WH6440> to shine<WH215> upon<WH854> us; Selah.<WH5542>
That thy way<WH1870> may be known<WH3045> upon earth,<WH776> thy saving health<WH3444> among all<WH3605> nations.<WH1471>
Let the people<WH5971> praise<WH3034> thee, O God;<WH430> let all<WH3605> the people<WH5971> praise<WH3034> thee.

O let the nations<WH3816> be glad<WH8055> and sing for joy:<WH7442> for<WH3588> thou shalt judge<WH8199> the people<WH5971> righteously,<WH4334> and govern<WH5148> the nations<WH3816> upon earth.<WH776> Selah.<WH5542>
Let the people<WH5971> praise<WH3034> thee, O God;<WH430> let all<WH3605> the people<WH5971> praise<WH3034> thee.
Then shall the earth<WH776> yield<WH5414> her increase;<WH2981> and God,<WH430> even our own God,<WH430> shall bless<WH1288> us.
God <WH430> shall bless<WH1288> us; and all<WH3605> the ends<WH657> of the earth<WH776> shall fear<WH3372> him.
